data.value: The building located on Liberty Island in New York is the most valuable symbol of the United States. The world-famous monument, built between 1875 and 1886, is the common work of famous architects Frederic Auguste Bartholdi, Gustave Eiffel, Richard Morris Hunt and Eugène Violetlet-Le-Duc. The monument, which is 93 meters high, is the work of the French, not the Americans, unlike many people think. The French made up of copper material, the monument of Liberty, the 100th anniversary of the founding of the country in the United States of America. they are gifts for the year. The head of the statue has a 7 pointed corner crown symbolizing the seven continents, a torch in his right hand, and a book on his left hand leaning on his gold sinker.
